{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-template-jsx","path":"/notimplemented-vs-notimplementederror-in-python","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<h1 id=\"what-is-notimplemented\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#what-is-notimplemented\" aria-label=\"what is notimplemented permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>What is NotImplemented?</h1>\n<p>The NotImplemented is built in constant in Python. It should be used by some of the python special methods for e.g (<strong>add</strong>(), <strong>eq</strong>()) to address that the operation is not implemented but can be run by other type. If this sounds confusing let's preview the use case of NotImplemented inside the python datetime standard library.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"python\"><pre class=\"language-python\"><code class=\"language-python\"> <span class=\"token keyword\">def</span> <span class=\"token function\">__add__</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>self<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> other<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span>\n        <span class=\"token keyword\">if</span> <span class=\"token builtin\">isinstance</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>other<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> timedelta<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span>\n            <span class=\"token comment\"># for CPython compatibility, we cannot use</span>\n            <span class=\"token comment\"># our __class__ here, but need a real timedelta</span>\n            <span class=\"token keyword\">return</span> timedelta<span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>self<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>_days <span class=\"token operator\">+</span> other<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>_days<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n                             self<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>_seconds <span class=\"token operator\">+</span> other<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>_seconds<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n                             self<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>_microseconds <span class=\"token operator\">+</span> other<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>_microseconds<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n        <span class=\"token keyword\">return</span> NotImplemented</code></pre></div>\n<p>The first line checks if the other object is timedelta, and if it is, it will return timedelta object that contains the time, seconds and microseconds of both objects. But if the other object is not timedelta, it doesn't throw an exception because, maybe the other object will know how to handle this operation. So, in short words the interpreter will try the <strong>add</strong> operation on the other type. If both attempts returne NotImplemented, then the appropriate exception will be raised.</p>\n<h1 id=\"the-notimplementederror-exception\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#the-notimplementederror-exception\" aria-label=\"the notimplementederror exception permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>The NotImplementedError exception</h1>\n<p>This is an exception that derives from the <a href=\"https://docs.python.org/3/library/exceptions.html#RuntimeError\">RuntimeError</a>. The usual use case of this exception is in the abstract class methods when they required the derived class to override them. </p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"python\"><pre class=\"language-python\"><code class=\"language-python\"><span class=\"token keyword\">class</span> <span class=\"token class-name\">Foo</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span>\n\n    <span class=\"token decorator annotation punctuation\">@property</span>\n    <span class=\"token keyword\">def</span> <span class=\"token function\">some_method</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>self<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span>\n        <span class=\"token keyword\">raise</span> NotImplementedError<span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">\"The derived class should implement the logic.\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span></code></pre></div>\n<p>Also, while developing you can raise this exception as a reminder to implement this method in the future. </p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"python\"><pre class=\"language-python\"><code class=\"language-python\"><span class=\"token keyword\">class</span> <span class=\"token class-name\">Foo</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span>\n\n    <span class=\"token comment\">#TODO</span>\n    <span class=\"token keyword\">def</span> <span class=\"token function\">new_method</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>self<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span>\n        <span class=\"token keyword\">raise</span> NotImplementedError<span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">\"Still not implemented.\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span></code></pre></div>","timeToRead":1,"excerpt":"What is NotImplemented? The NotImplemented is built in constant in Python. It should be used by some of the python special methods for e.g…","frontmatter":{"title":"NotImplemented vs NotImplementedError in Python","date":"2020-05-26 21:27:54 +0200","categories":["python"],"tags":["python","exceptions"],"description":null,"keywords":"python, exceptions","author":"Zoran Pandovski","cover":{"childImageSharp":{"fixed":{"base64":"data:image/png;base64,iVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAABQAAAAPCAYAAADkmO9VAAAACXBIWXMAAAsTAAALEwEAmpwYAAAAZ0lEQVQ4y2Mw5v//n5qYYdRAODbiw60JnxwDPg2GvAhsBKP58BuK04UgzRai//9biUNoM2EIbSJAhgtBWJ/r/3831f//Yx3//4+w/v8/yvb//2i7//+tJSCWDbyXqRopNDFwNOsRjQHOdKSa6R2eoAAAAABJRU5ErkJggg==","width":540,"height":400,"src":"/static/18b0edfdfa96fadbadd7955f1202cbd7/819a5/python.png","srcSet":"/static/18b0edfdfa96fadbadd7955f1202cbd7/819a5/python.png 1x"}}}},"fields":{"slug":"/notimplemented-vs-notimplementederror-in-python","date":"2020-05-26T19:27:54.000Z"}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/notimplemented-vs-notimplementederror-in-python","nexttitle":"How to list `dot` files in Linux","nextslug":"/how-to-list-dot-files-in-linux","prevtitle":"Check if a string contains substring in Python","prevslug":"/check-if-a-string-contains-substring-in-python","tagList":["abstraction","OOP","Class","java","collection","API","Map","HashMap","LinkedHashMap","TreeMap","Python","cli","args","argparse","javascript","es6","beginner","codenewbie","Primary_key","implementation","Composite_key","language-support","localization","internationalization","linux","file permissions","Project Euler","Algortithms","SQL","database","commands","GO","Datatypes","Variables","Constants","